Is there any documentation of the "substance_flag" function called by 
liquidvapor.cti? As each of the 5 calls are unique, there's got to be 
a file somewhere that's got the saturationrelations for these 5 
fluids. I'd love to add ammonia (and H2O2 perhaps) to this file.

Any thought of changing the (or adding a new) NASA embedded 
description to use the "new" 9 coeffient representation of species? 
Is there any reason to even bother?

I'm starting a project on the side to help an undergrad group with a 
project here involving rockets. If anyone here has any references to 
reaction databases involving solid rocket motors (especially Aluminum-
related) I'd appreciate any information.

Chad
